name: 91 Krypt
description: 91 Krypt by DNA Genetics is a potent strain by many names. Bred from the Chemdawg ‘91 stock crossed with DNA’s famous Captain Krypt OG, this strain was created for high potency cannabis consumers. It emits a deep, dank terpene profile that fills the room with skunk and swampy earth. With a THC content pushing over 20% on average, enjoy 91 Krypt to stimulate appetite while harnessing full body relaxation.

highlightedReviews.text:
This strain was obtained by Tweed

To start, this is a green house (sun-grown) strain so it's buds look different off the back. We will include picture late hopefully. The buds look dark green, but they look like the typical "weed you got from the guy down the street" kind of weed. It looks home grown, but if done well. 

The smell is sort of a sweet but musky smell, which doesn't overfill your space with the smell. It's also a very well cured bud, which Tweed holds that standard, but we've experience dry bud before. 

The smoke isn't harsh, which is good because sometimes it can be a little hashy I've found. The smoke also isn't too smelly either, so easy to mask which is important!

The high took about 10 minutes to kick in, which is actually weird because usually it hits in right away or second later. It was a creeper high, but it was a surprising head high at first. Behind the eyes and cerebral around the back of the head tingled. It was a calming and soon body calming feel. It was almost soothing for sore muscles, but more of the hybrid feeling so not overly strong. 

There wasn't any negative effects, but maybe munchies. Most indicas are Manchy strains, but this one was one that you knew it would be. 

All around we gave it a 5/5 and if you see it in the future or at Tweed, maybe get some?
Fast head hitting high that slowly mellows down to more of a weightless feeling, leaving you floating amongst yourself.
